                <head>286. Summary of Conclusions of a Special Coordination Committee (Intelligence)
                        Meeting<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d286fn1">Source: National Security
                        Council, Carter Administration Intelligence Files, Box I020, Minutes—<gloss
                            target="#t_SCC_1">SCC</gloss> 1978. Secret; Senstive. The meeting took
                        place in the White House Situation Room. <persName corresp="#p_GD_1"
                            >Gregg</persName> sent the summary to <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                            >Brzezinski</persName> under a July 17 covering memorandum requesting
                        that <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1">Brzezinski</persName> approve the summary
                        and forward a Presidential Finding to Carter for his approval. For
                        additional information about the finding, see <ref target="#d286fn3"
                            >footnote 3</ref> below. <persName corresp="#p_BZ_1"
                            >Brzezinski</persName> approved the summary and indicated that it should
                        be distributed to the <gloss target="#t_CIA_1">CIA</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            from="1979-07-17T15:30:00-04:00" to="1979-07-17T16:30:00-04:00">July 17,
                            1979, 3:30–4:30 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
